## Merge the extracted files and find the Average weekly Sales corresponding to each Store.
data = train.merge(features,on = ['Store','Date'],how ='inner').merge(store,on=['Store'],how='inner')
labels = np.unique(data['Type'].values)
colors = ['yellow','green','lightcoral']
def get_sum(df):
    return ((np.sum(df['Weekly_Sales'])) / len(df['Weekly_Sales']))
data = data.sort_values(['Type'],ascending=[True])    
value_grps = data.groupby(['Type']).apply(get_sum)
explode = (0.1,0,0)
plt.pie(value_grps, explode=explode, labels=labels, colors=colors,
autopct='%1.1f%%', shadow=True, startangle=140)
plt.legend(labels, loc="best")
plt.axis('equal')
plt.show()

## Average year wise sales per year.
data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'])
data['Year'] = data['Date'].dt.year
data['Month'] = data['Date'].dt.month
data['Week'] = data['Date'].dt.week
data['Day'] = data['Date'].dt.day
year_labels = np.unique(data['Year'].values)
data['n_days'] = (data['Date'].dt.date - data['Date'].dt.date.min()).apply(lambda x : x.days)
weekly_sales_2010 = data[data['Year'] == 2010]['Weekly_Sales'].groupby(data['Week']).mean()
weekly_sales_2011 = data[data['Year'] == 2011]['Weekly_Sales'].groupby(data['Week']).mean()
weekly_sales_2012 = data[data['Year'] == 2012]['Weekly_Sales'].groupby(data['Week']).mean()
plt.figure(figsize=(20,8))
sns.lineplot(weekly_sales_2010.index, weekly_sales_2010.values)
sns.lineplot(weekly_sales_2011.index, weekly_sales_2011.values)
sns.lineplot(weekly_sales_2012.index, weekly_sales_2012.values)
plt.grid()
plt.xticks(np.arange(1, 53, step=1))
plt.legend(year_labels, loc='best', fontsize=16)
plt.title('Average Weekly Sales - Per Year', fontsize=18)
plt.ylabel('Sales', fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel('Week', fontsize=16)

#Modelling the dataset. Keeping the target variable as Weekly_Sales corresponding to the walmart. 

# Different predictors used inorder to detect the weekly sales of the walmart are as follows :-
#1. Store
#2. Dept
#3. Temperature
#4. Fuel Price
#5. CPI
#6. Unemployment    

data = data[data['Weekly_Sales'] > 0]
columns = ["Store","Dept","Temperature","Fuel_Price","CPI","Unemployment"]
new_data = data[columns]

minmax_scaler = MinMaxScaler()
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(new_data, data['Weekly_Sales'])

y_train = minmax_scaler.fit_transform(y_train.values[:,None])[:, 0]
y_test = minmax_scaler.transform(y_test.values[:,None])[:, 0]


alphas = [0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3, 1.0, 10.0, 100.0, 300.0, 500.0, 1e3, 1.5e3, 2e3, 5e3, 1e4]
alphas_log_10 = np.log10(alphas)
min_rmse_ridge = np.inf 
best_alpha_ridge = 0


for index in range(len(alphas_log_10)):
    reg = Ridge(alphas[index],True)
    non_zero_coff,norm_coff = reg.fit(X_train.values,y_train)
    rmse = reg.evaluate(X_test.values,y_test)  

    if(rmse < min_rmse_ridge):
        min_rmse_ridge = rmse
        best_alpha_ridge = alphas[index]
        
         
ridge = Ridge(best_alpha_ridge,True)
non_zero_coff,norm_coff = ridge.fit(X_train.values,y_train)
mean_square_error = ridge.evaluate(X_test.values,y_test)
print('Mean sqaure error Ridge :',mean_square_error)


min_rmse_lasso = np.inf 
best_alpha_lasso = 0


for index in range(len(alphas_log_10)):
    lasso = Lasso(alphas[index],True)
    non_zero_coff,norm_coff = lasso.fit(X_train.values,y_train)
    rmse = lasso.evaluate(X_test.values,y_test)  

    if(rmse < min_rmse_lasso):
        min_rmse_lasso = rmse
        best_alpha_lasso = alphas[index]


lasso = Lasso(best_alpha_lasso,True)
non_zero_coff,norm_coff = lasso.fit(X_train.values,y_train)
mean_square_error = lasso.evaluate(X_test.values,y_test)
print('Mean square error Lasso :',mean_square_error)


min_rmse_Elastic = np.inf
best_alpha_elatic = 0


for index in range(len(alphas_log_10)):
    elastic = Elastic(alphas[index],True)
    non_zero_coff,norm_coff = elastic.fit(X_train.values,y_train)
    rmse = elastic.evaluate(X_test.values,y_test)  

    if(rmse < min_rmse_lasso):
        min_rmse_Elastic = rmse
        best_alpha_elatic = alphas[index]

elastic = Elastic(best_alpha_elatic,True)
non_zero_coff,norm_coff = elastic.fit(X_train.values,y_train)
mean_square_error = elastic.evaluate(X_test.values,y_test)
print('Mean square error Elatic :',mean_square_error)


min_rmse_baseline = np.inf
best_alpha_linear = 0


linear_reg = LinearRegression(True)
non_zero_coff,norm_coff = linear_reg.fit(X_train.values,y_train)
mean_square_error = linear_reg.evaluate(X_test.values,y_test)
print('Mean square error Linear Regression :',mean_square_error)      

print("The mean sqaure error of Ridge regression is minimum, hence it is preffered over other models")

Mean sqaure error Ridge : 0.03229441613105233
